comment_data.body: I get the same error when I use InteliJ IDEA
@helin24 we don't yet provide M1 builds of JxBrowser, but it works fine in Rosetta mode.

@vlad-lubenskyi thanks for catching this! Do you know if we can detect M1 and Rosetta mode from Java? 

@alex-pricope can you verify that this error does not occur in Rosetta mode?

> @alex-pricope can you verify that this error does not occur in Rosetta mode?

The option to run in Rosetta is missing from the app properties. This means it's native right? 

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/22158971/117875887-faf8fd80-b2a2-11eb-995c-bf691ec00305.png)

@alex-pricope I'm not sure, I may need to consult with JetBrains about this and get back to you. It looks like they released a version of IntelliJ for M1 in an earlier version (2020.3) so I believe that means your version is native. Thanks for checking, I'll look into this.

@alex-pricope I confirmed that your version is native, so it does not have the option to run with Rosetta. I'm going to turn off the embedded browser when using the M1 version of IntelliJ. If you'd prefer to use the embedded browser, you can download the Intel version (e.g. in downloads https://www.jetbrains.com/idea/download/#section=mac there's a dropdown menu to choose either '.dmg (Intel)' or '.dmg (Apple Silicon)').

title: Plugin error at running default new flutter app on M1
